values: tell me why this jcs concert was freakin' awesome!   sev was there and they sang that one song from the pepsi blue commercial...  and this other group called gold mind squad, but the lead singer was a little... hmmm....  feminine....  but he was cool though.  lots of screaming.  these loser guys in the front started moshing and stomped on this other guys face.  i felt bad...  but that's cuz boys are stupid...  i'm sitting there with my dad being a big honkin' DORK!!!  but i don't care cuz i love my daddy...  and then jimmie's chicken shack came out, and they were so awesome.  it was great.  jimmie hoppa was such a cutie, but he shaved his head and i wasn't feeling that.  and they started making fun of creed, and that made me laugh cuz creed sux!  i was scared for my life.  DC is scary like some stuff.  all the homeless peeps just flocked to us.  very scary.  and my bud laura was there, and we gave her a ride home b/c i didn't want her to get killed riding the metro home at 1 in the morning.  but yeah.  in other news....  the period is 2 days late, so we're freakin' out......  :(  very scary!  i don't want to get too worried, but i've never been late before, not in 7 years...

we just went out for lunch and i had a ham sandwich while raed's dad berated me about stupid crap like grades....  is he my dad?  speaking of which, my daddy isn't home yet and it makes me sad  :(  but yeah.  i'm trying to go to einstein's tomorrow and get a chicken sandwich with raspberry mustard...  mmmm....  yummy....  but yeah...  again, newspaper is the most broing class ever....  that's why i'm on here doing... nothing...  but yeah.  i g2g........

i'm home now....  that walk was killer...  halfway through it i thought my legs were going to fall off of my body....  but i'm cool now.  trying to make some crab cakes, but i'm afraid of using hot oil to fry them...  anyway....  so much to do!  i decided i'm a part of the procrastination generation....  that's what i've deemed our generation, so i hope everyone is happy.  my mom and my brother aren't here, so it's blissfully quiet...  my yearbook teacher is beig a big biatch...  but it's cuz the computers are stupid, and she expects me to know how to fix it, and when i don't, it's like, the end of the world, and she gets super pissed and gets all smarmy with me...  grrr...  the pressures of high school.  how fun...  and my friend mikey came up from arizona (spring break for collegiates)  and that was cool.  he makes me happy.  my daddy's somewhere in florida, and he's supposed to be coming home tonite.  what a big b'jerk!  so....  yeah.  i've decided to open my own clothing store.  it's gonna be super bitchin....  but yeah.  i guess i'll be going off to fry up my crab cakes now... hope i don't burn my face off..  prom is coming up too!  i so have ADD...

ugh!  i'm so tired.  life is so busy right now, and i tried to register for the SAT online, but then our computers at school wouldn't work, and then, i forgot my fee form!  and i have to walk home in a minute, and i'm kinda all by myself, and it sucks to walk home, in general.  yearbook is biting  the big one, as we missed our deadline for the whole book to be printed, so now we're moving in double time...  basically, i'm tired, and frustrated, things just aren't going my way right now...  maybe next week will be better.  and now i've got to get off the computer, so bye! :)

school is, again, biting the big one.  i'm in newspaper....again, and my articles suck and my word counts are like, a bajillion words...... :( my back hurts....  all i do is complain.  friendships are waning right now all over the place and i don't know why...  maybe i'm just paranoid....  my eyes hurt...  air pressue or something.  we had school off for 10 day last week and that was pretty freakin awesome, but then i got bored and the snow was ugly...  and my room was cold.  i signed up for this creative writing course for senior year (next year), but when i went to the meeting, the classroom smelled, like, beyond bad.  like dirty ass... or something....  and it was just awful, i wanted to puke... and apparently, it was the teacher.  so instantly, i felt bad, but i didn't want to be rude so i didn't say anything...  but it was umm...  horrible.  me and raed are doing cool (2 yrs in january)....just some stuff with his parents and birth control.  they're going psycho cuz they don't want me to get pregnant or something, but we're not even doing anything, so i don't know what the deal is.  his dad won't even let me come over unless he sees a slip from a clinic for a perscription....  what a dickhead.  but yeah, that's the news on the  raed front.  all my firneds hate him, but i think a lot of it is jealousy.  it's hard for me to understand because i want to be friends with everyone.  and i want my firends to be friends with everyone, but i know i can't control everyone.  grr.....  i wore my cute little rainbow brite hoodie today and this ghetto little boy asked me if i was gay.  some people just don't get it....  emily still doesn't want to be friends with me, and just to give y'all the skippy.  back in october, she found condoms in my purse (i wasn't using them, just had them), and she was all freaked out and mad because i hadn't told her, but she's a jehovah's witness, and so she has some very "set in stone"-ish beliefs, and so instantly she was saying i was a bitch and all this stuff because i hid basically my whole love life from her, but i had my reasons, you know?  i knew she would disapprove, but in my mind, if i'm going to do it, i might as well be safe, right?  but that's beside the point.  that was way back in october (of last year) and we talked about it on aim that nite i belive, but we got nowhere because she said "you always do this, you never tell me the truth, you always hurt me"....blase blase, but i couldn't talk to her anymore about it because i got a very parent-like lecture, and i don't need that from my best friend...  well... ex-best friend.  so she called me up about three days later and told me that she thought she needed her space and that she wasn't going to see me again, basically telling me to stop calling until whenever, and you know, that's crushing to hear from anyone, let alone my best friend of 7 years.  so i've talked to her sporatically (once every two or three months), and i get occasional e-mails, but things have been very tense and the converstaions are always awkward and unhappy.  but it was so unfair to me.  and it hurts so much.  but we're kind of getting back...  i think.  her last e-mail didn't sound too bad.  i could be mistaken though.  but yeah, i don't tink i have much more time (the bell's going to ring), but i'll write more when i get the chance, and hopefully, it won't take as long fo rme to get back on here....  so yeah...  adios

i'm stuck here in newspaper (which is the most boring class on the entire planet for the first month) and i don't think this school year could get any worse.  i have five different textbooks and no locker (mine won't open)....my best friend called me an idiot yesterday (when she was SO wrong)....my boyfriend's all preoccupied with football, and i'm so tired, i think i might quit my job.  but then i want the money, so maybe i won't.  but maybe i will.  i have a feeling i'm going to have to work a lot this weekend, and i really don't want to....but what are you going to do?  AP modern world is really boring (i fell asleep yesterday), and ap english is hard becuase i don't want to show up my boyfriend cuz he's really bad with english classes.  but i don't know.  there are over 500 stupid little freshman in my school and the other day they ran out of lunch in the cafeteria...  my back hurts, and my feet hurt, and i'm so frustrated about everything that i don't know what to do.  excpet newspaper.  i can chill out in here (in the office), but whatever.  gotta go, cuz the period's alomost over.  talk to ya later, and ash, i'll write you soon, if you're readig this....

what a crusty day...  i haven't been online in the longest time.  i'm such a loser!  work is getting on my nerves and school is getting on my nerves, b/c the plague is the boringest book in the whole freaking universe... i never have anything good to talk about, but i promised myself that i would use this...  what can i say?  my mother is a complete lunatic and freaks out about EVERYTHING, i can never win any arguments, even though i am the obvious victor...  life really sucked last nite cuz i won this facial thing from mary kay (through my work), and this lady was going to come over to my house to give me this gift certificate thing and then my mom started freaking ourt and called the lady up and bitched her out.  sometimes i wonder why i tell her anything...  my brother is crazy, but what's new?  i'm worried about him for this next school year, but then he's such a jerk to me and i don't even care.  grrrr....  i hate to think about dying, but the thoughts often pass through my head.  i'm so twisted.  but i can't help it.  it's not serious thoughts, just little notions.  i'm so wierd.  and i worry too much.  and i talk to much.  and i'm tired...  see?  i got up at, like, 1:30...  but i stayed up till 4 so it's not like i got a million hours of sleep.  anywayz, i better get off of here before my mom gets home and rips me a new one!

yes, i realize i just wrote an entry two seconds ago, but then i found out you could do cool stuff (and by cool i mean that you can put a mood...i'm such a dork!)  anywayz, yeah, i'm leaving tomorrow. :( how sad.  i hope i can come back sooner though.  my crazy mommy might not let me.  and she really is crazy...

ummm.....this is my first entry, cuz i'm a loosah!  but this is pretty cool, and maybe i'll actually use it.  maybe not...  i'm in NC with ashalee my bud, and i haven't been  here for three years.  so it's cool.  but anywayz, i just wanted to try this out...so...bye!
